  "markdown": "[Skip to main content](https://9to5google.com/2026/02/17/youtube-outage-february-2026/#main)\n\n- [YouTube](https://9to5google.com/guides/youtube/)\n\n# It’s not just you, YouTube is partially down in outage\n\n[![Avatar for Ben Schoon](https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/59cb0e121a572a78cfc8040731068741887591b7ef93f5498a8d93310278c0f7?s=30&d=mm&r=r)](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/) [Ben Schoon](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/ \"Posts by Ben Schoon\") \\| Feb 17 2026 - 5:27 pm PT\n\n[105 Comments](https://9to5google.com/2026/02/17/youtube-outage-february-2026/#comments)\n\n![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/YouTube-Logo-App-2.jpg?quality=82&strip=all&w=1600)\n\nIf you’re trying to access YouTube right now and running into problems, you’re not alone, as a widespread outage appears to be affecting YouTube and, to a lesser extent, YouTube TV.\n\n* * *\n\n**Update:** Google says that this issue is partially fixed, with the homepage once again accessible, but a “full fix” is yet to come for issues affecting recommendations.\n\n> An issue with our recommendations system prevented videos from appearing across surfaces on YouTube (including the homepage, the YouTube app, YouTube Music and YouTube Kids). The homepage is back, but we’re still working on a full fix.\n\n* * *\n\nStarting at around 7:45pm ET (4:45pm PT) and expanding rapidly as of 8pm ET (5pm PT), YouTube is down in a fairly widespread outage. There are nearly 300,000 reports [on _DownDetector_](https://downdetector.com/status/youtube/) and growing, with a large spike for both [Google](https://downdetector.com/status/google/) and [YouTube TV](https://downdetector.com/status/youtube-tv/) on the outage tracker as well – as far as we can tell, though, this is primarily a core YouTube outage.\n\nThe outage is being [widely reported across](https://www.reddit.com/r/youtube/new/) [social media](https://x.com/TeamYouTube/with_replies), as well as members of the _9to5_ team. In testing, we’ve been unable to access core features of YouTube including the subscription feed, Shorts, and even the homepage both through the mobile app and the web app. YouTube TV remains accessible in our tests, and YouTube Music seems to be working as well.\n\nAdvertisement - scroll for more content\n\nNotably, this doesn’t appear to be affecting YouTube videos accessed through direct links or embeds, at least through the web.\n\n- ![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/image_c4799b.png?w=1024)\n- ![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/Screenshot_20260217_202654_YouTube.jpg?quality=82&strip=all)\n\nAs of 8:20pm ET (5:20pm PT), Google has yet to formally acknowledge the outage.\n\n![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/image_414e75.png)\n\n_Updating…_\n\n[![Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/themes/ninetofive/dist/images/google-preferred-source-badge-dark.png)![Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/themes/ninetofive/dist/images/google-preferred-source-badge-light.png)](https://google.com/preferences/source?q=https://9to5google.com)\n\n_FTC: We use income earning auto affiliate links._ [More.](https://9to5mac.com/about/#affiliate)\n\n[![](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/native-banner_750_150.jpg?quality=82&strip=all&w=700)](https://benqurl.biz/3WZyqpL)\n\nYou’re reading 9to5Google — experts who break news about Google and its surrounding ecosystem, day after day. Be sure to check out [our homepage](http://9to5google.com/) for all the latest news, and follow 9to5Google on [Twitter](http://twitter.com/9to5google), [Facebook](http://facebook.com/9to5google), and [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/9to5google.com/) to stay in the loop. Don’t know where to start? Check out our [exclusive stories](https://9to5google.com/feature/exclusive/), [reviews](https://9to5google.com/guides/reviews/), [how-tos](https://9to5google.com/guides/how-to/), and [subscribe to our YouTube channel](https://www.youtube.com/9to5google)\n\n[_Check out 9to5Google on YouTube for more news:_](https://www.youtube.com/c/9to5google?sub_confirmation=1)\n\n## Comments\n\n![conversation-loading](https://static-cdn.spot.im/production/social/tags/v5.24.3/launcher/ec24cb303220fcfc94f8.svg)\n\nExpandClose comments\n\nExpandClose comments\n\n## Guides\n\n[![YouTube](https://9to5google.com/wp-content/client-mu-plugins/9to5-core/includes/obfuscate-images/images/9to5google-default.jpg?quality=82&strip=all&w=140)\\\\\n\\\\\n**YouTube** \\\\\n\\\\\nYouTube is Google's massive video streaming plat…](https://9to5google.com/guides/youtube/)\n\n## Author\n\n[![Avatar for Ben Schoon](https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/59cb0e121a572a78cfc8040731068741887591b7ef93f5498a8d93310278c0f7?s=82&d=mm&r=r)](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/)[Ben Schoon](https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/) [nexusben](https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=nexusben&original_referer=https%3A%2F%2F9to5google.com)\n\nBen is a Senior Editor for 9to5Google.\n\nFind him on Twitter @NexusBen. Send tips to schoon@9to5g.com or encrypted to benschoon@protonmail.com.\n\nSubscribe to notifications",
  "html": "<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en-US\" class=\"js\" style=\"--header-bottom-height: 26087px; --scrollbar-width: 15px;\">\n\t<body class=\"wp-singular post-template-default single single-post postid-704793 single-format-standard wp-embed-responsive wp-theme-ninetofive ninetofive-sub-site color-scheme-google ninetofive-google infinite-scroll neverending\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\t<!-- Google Tag Manager (noscript) -->\n\t\t\n\t\t<!-- End Google Tag Manager (noscript) -->\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<!-- Google Tag Manager (noscript) -->\n\t\t\n\t\t<!-- End Google Tag Manager (noscript) -->\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<a href=\"https://9to5google.com/2026/02/17/youtube-outage-february-2026/#main\" class=\"skip-to-content-link visually-hidden-focusable\">Skip to main content</a>\n\n\t\t\n\n\n\n\t\t<main id=\"main\" role=\"main\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"th3d8381b3 ad-container ad-container--leaderboard order-control__mobile-top\">\n\t<div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1436850350386-0\" class=\"inlinead\"></div>\t\n\t</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"container med left\">\n\t\t\t\t<ul class=\"article__meta-guides fs-xs\">\n\t\t\t<li class=\"meta__guide\"><a href=\"https://9to5google.com/guides/youtube/\">YouTube</a></li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h1 class=\"h1\">It’s not just you, YouTube is partially down in outage</h1>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-meta flex fs-sm\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"plain author-image flex center\" href=\"https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img alt=\"Avatar for Ben Schoon\" src=\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/59cb0e121a572a78cfc8040731068741887591b7ef93f5498a8d93310278c0f7?s=30&amp;d=mm&amp;r=r\" class=\"avatar avatar-30 photo author-gravatar\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" decoding=\"async\">\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"author-name\"><a href=\"https://9to5google.com/author/nexusben1/\" title=\"Posts by Ben Schoon\" rel=\"author\">Ben Schoon</a></span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;Feb 17 2026 - 5:27 pm PT\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"meta__comment-count\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://9to5google.com/2026/02/17/youtube-outage-february-2026/#comments\" id=\"single-comments-link\" class=\"comments flex\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 30 30\" class=\"icon-comment\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M0 0v19.139h5v4.784h5V30l7.94-6.077H30V4.785h-5V0zm2.5 2.392h20v2.393H5v11.961H2.5zm5 4.785h20v14.354H17.06l-4.56 3.49v-3.49h-5zm3.75 3.589v2.392h12.5v-2.392zm0 4.784v2.392h7.5V15.55z\"></path></svg>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t105 Comments\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div id=\"river\" class=\"river\">\n\t\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"container flex-lg\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"container med post-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure class=\"img-border featured-image\">\n\n\t<img width=\"1600\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/YouTube-Logo-App-2.jpg?quality=82&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1600\" class=\"skip-lazy wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\">\n\t</figure>\n\n<p>If you’re trying to access YouTube right now and running into problems, you’re not alone, as a widespread outage appears to be affecting YouTube and, to a lesser extent, YouTube TV.</p>\n\n\n\n<span id=\"more-704793\"></span>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\">\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Update:</strong> Google says that this issue is partially fixed, with the homepage once again accessible, but a “full fix” is yet to come for issues affecting recommendations.</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<p>An issue with our recommendations system prevented videos from appearing across surfaces on YouTube (including the homepage, the YouTube app, YouTube Music and YouTube Kids). The homepage is back, but we’re still working on a full fix.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\">\n\n\n\n<p>Starting at around 7:45pm ET (4:45pm PT) and expanding rapidly as of 8pm ET (5pm PT), YouTube is down in a fairly widespread outage. There are nearly 300,000 reports <a href=\"https://downdetector.com/status/youtube/\">on <em>DownDetector</em></a> and growing, with a large spike for both <a href=\"https://downdetector.com/status/google/\">Google </a>and<a href=\"https://downdetector.com/status/youtube-tv/\"> YouTube TV</a> on the outage tracker as well – as far as we can tell, though, this is primarily a core YouTube outage.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The outage is being <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/youtube/new/\">widely reported across</a> <a href=\"https://x.com/TeamYouTube/with_replies\">social media</a>, as well as members of the <em>9to5</em> team. In testing, we’ve been unable to access core features of YouTube including the subscription feed, Shorts, and even the homepage both through the mobile app and the web app. YouTube TV remains accessible in our tests, and YouTube Music seems to be working as well.</p>\t<span class=\"outbrain-ad-label\">Advertisement - scroll for more content</span>\n\t<div id=\"div-gpt-ad-outbrain-ad-704793\" class=\"th15159a1e thec410445\" data-outbrain=\"\" data-post-id=\"704793\">\n\t\t\n\t</div>\n\t\n\n\n\n<p>Notably, this doesn’t appear to be affecting YouTube videos accessed through direct links or embeds, at least through the web.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow aligncenter\" data-autoplay=\"true\" data-delay=\"4\" data-effect=\"slide\" data-jetpack-block-initialized=\"true\"><div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_container swiper swiper-initialized swiper-horizontal swiper-backface-hidden wp-swiper-initialized\"><ul class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_swiper-wrapper swiper-wrapper\" style=\"width: 3808px; cursor: grab; transform: translate3d(0px, 0px, 0px); height: 793px;\" id=\"swiper-wrapper-82d8caf84beb70a5\" aria-live=\"off\"><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide swiper-slide-active\" style=\"width: 1904px;\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"1 / 2\" data-swiper-slide-index=\"0\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"-1\"><figure><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1281\" height=\"734\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-704797\" data-id=\"704797\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/image_c4799b.png?w=1024\"></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide swiper-slide-next\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"2 / 2\" data-swiper-slide-index=\"1\" style=\"width: 1904px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1968\" height=\"2184\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-704798\" data-id=\"704798\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1024 / 1136\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/Screenshot_20260217_202654_YouTube.jpg?quality=82&amp;strip=all\"></figure></li></ul><a class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-prev swiper-button-prev swiper-button-white swiper-button-disabled\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"Previous slide\" aria-controls=\"swiper-wrapper-82d8caf84beb70a5\" style=\"top: 396px;\"></a><a class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-next swiper-button-next swiper-button-white\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"Next slide\" aria-controls=\"swiper-wrapper-82d8caf84beb70a5\" style=\"top: 396px;\"></a><a aria-label=\"Pause Slideshow\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-pause\" role=\"button\"></a><div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_pagination swiper-pagination swiper-pagination-white swiper-pagination-custom swiper-pagination-horizontal\"><button class=\"swiper-pagination-bullet swiper-pagination-bullet-active\" tab-index=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-label=\"Go to slide 1\"></button><button class=\"swiper-pagination-bullet\" tab-index=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-label=\"Go to slide 2\"></button></div><span class=\"swiper-notification\" aria-live=\"assertive\" aria-atomic=\"true\"></span></div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>As of 8:20pm ET (5:20pm PT), Google has yet to formally acknowledge the outage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignwide size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"985\" height=\"421\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/image_414e75.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-704796\"></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Updating…</em></p>\n\t<div class=\"google-preferred-source-badge\">\n\t\t<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://google.com/preferences/source?q=https://9to5google.com\" aria-label=\"Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google\">\n\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"google-preferred-source-badge-dark\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/themes/ninetofive/dist/images/google-preferred-source-badge-dark.png\" alt=\"Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google\">\n\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"google-preferred-source-badge-light\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/themes/ninetofive/dist/images/google-preferred-source-badge-light.png\" alt=\"Add 9to5Google as a preferred source on Google\">\n\t\t</a>\n\t</div>\n\t<div class=\"ad-disclaimer-container\"><p class=\"disclaimer-affiliate\"><em>FTC: We use income earning auto affiliate links.</em> <a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/about/#affiliate\">More.</a></p><a href=\"https://benqurl.biz/3WZyqpL\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-704145\" src=\"https://9to5google.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/02/native-banner_750_150.jpg?quality=82&amp;strip=all&amp;w=700\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"140\"></a></div><div id=\"after_disclaimer_placement\"><div class=\"visitor-promo\" data-nosnippet=\"true\">You’re reading 9to5Google — experts who break news about Google and its surrounding ecosystem, day after day. Be sure to check out <a href=\"http://9to5google.com/\">our homepage</a> for all the latest news, and follow 9to5Google 